item.title: SciPipe used at NASA Glenn Research Center
item.description: I was happy to see the publication finally going online , of work done at NASA Glenn Research Center , where SciPipe has been used to process and track provenance of the analyses, “Modeling the impact of thoracic pressure on intracranial pressure”. I’ve known the work existed for a couple of years, after getting some extraordinarily useful contributions from Drayton fixing some bugs I’m not sure I’d ever find otherwise, but cool to now also see it published!
